  "texts": [
    "In the following, we show the mAP and NDS of t-READi under different missing modality scenarios.",
    "On the x-axis of the figures, \"Full\" denotes there are no missing sensors, and \"number+C/L\" denotes the number of remaining cameras and lidars (there is a total of 6 cameras and 1 lidar).a) Missing camera.",
    ": We first present how our contrastive learning framework deals with missing cameras.",
    "It can be seen in Figure 12 that mAP and NDS under contrastive learning decrease from 0.71 to 0.59 and from 0.68 to 0.60, respectively, and the mAP and NDS under zero filling decrease from 0.72 to 0.52 and from 0.68 to 0.53, respectively.",
    "Although we can still observe mAP and NDS decrease when contrastive learning is adopted, the decreased mAP and NDS is smaller than those of zero filling, proving t-READi's robustness to missing modalities."
  ],
